        <div class="content-main">

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Overview</span><h2>Senior Citizen FD: Higher Rates for Retirees</h2></div>
            <p>All banks and NBFCs in India offer preferential fixed deposit interest rates for senior citizens (aged 60 years and above). This additional interest of 0.25% to 0.50% over regular rates is designed to support retirees who depend on FD interest as their primary source of income. Some banks even offer an additional premium for super senior citizens (80+).</p>
            <p>For senior citizens, FDs remain the safest and most reliable investment option. With rates going up to 8.30% at NBFCs like Bajaj Finance, a ₹50 lakh deposit can generate over ₹4 lakh annually in interest income — sufficient to cover a significant portion of living expenses. The higher TDS threshold of ₹50,000 (vs ₹40,000 for others) provides additional tax relief.</p>
            <p>When choosing a senior citizen FD, consider factors beyond just the interest rate: DICGC coverage, premature withdrawal flexibility, monthly interest payout option, and auto-renewal terms. A diversified FD portfolio across 2–3 banks ensures both safety and optimal returns.</p>
          </div>

